               <head>Sermones de sanctis, etc.; Michael de Massa, <title>Super Passionem</title>; Jacobus de Voragine, <title>Legenda Aurea</title>. Germany: A 1405, B 15th century, first quarter, C 14th century, second half </head>
               <physDesc>
                  <p n="composite">Composite: three parts</p>
                  <p><secFol>eleuatum</secFol></p>
                  <objectDesc>
                     <supportDesc>
                        <extent>235 (154 + 26 + 55) fols. (foliated 1–234, 57 is double) <dimensions type="leaf" unit="mm">
                              <height>300</height>
                              <width max="215" min="210">210–15</width>
                           </dimensions>
                        </extent>
                     </supportDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <musicNotation>
                     <p>Offsets on the lower board from a fourteenth-century (?) liturgical manuscript with musical notation; fragments of the same manuscript in the binding.</p>
                  </musicNotation>
                  <bindingDesc>
                     <binding notAfter="1450" notBefore="1400">
                        <p>Early (?) fifteenth-century binding of plain pigskin over boards; remains of title written on the upper cover; clasp lost; bosses on the upper and lower boards lost.</p>
                     </binding>
                  </bindingDesc>
                  <accMat>See above (musical notation); fragments of other manuscripts used for repair and quire-strengtheners.</accMat>
               </physDesc>
