                     <msItem n="1" xml:id="MS_Hamilton_14-part3-item1">
                        <locus>(fols. 180ra-234vb)</locus>
                        <author key="person_100198644"><supplied>Jacobus de Voragine</supplied></author>
                        <title key="work_2330"><supplied>Legenda aurea</supplied></title>
                        <note>(imperfect)</note>
                        <rubric>De aduentu domini</rubric>
                        <incipit>Universum tempus presentis vite in iiijor distingwitur</incipit>
                        <note>Graesse, cc. 1 (treated as one unit with the prologue), 2 (sections 1–9), St Barbara (see below), 3 (ending 'omnibus generatur', Graesse p. 29); Conception of the Virgin (see below), 4–8, <!-- image 392, fol. 190v -->, 9 (sections 1–12), 10–11, 12 (without the prologue), 13 (ending 'rediit ad locum suum', Graesse p. 86), 14–17, 19, 21, 22–26, 28, 31 (with the preceding paragraph 'De festivitatibus'), 32–36, 37 (section 1 only), 38–39, 210 (207, Dorothy, varied), <!-- check here --> 42–44, 45 (ending 'populo demonstratur', Graesse p. 187), 46 (sections 1–17), 47, Gertrude (see below), 49–51, 53–58, Passio S. Georgii (see below), 59 (ending shortly after the beginning of sect. 2), 61, 63 (ends imperfect, fol. 233vb 'die fuisset sepultum. Plura et ||', cf. Graesse p. 283 near bottom). Fol. 234r-v contains part of c. 67, St James the Less, 'sicut in calcaneis ... monicionibus conuerterentur', Grasse pp. 296–9.</note>
                        <note>Often shorter than the text printed in Graesse. Many chapters are followed by a paragraph of 'merita' summarizing or giving additional reasons for a saint's veneration, e.g. (fol. 184rb) 'sancta barbara habet sibi omnes seruientes a subita morte custodire...', (fol. 186va) 'Sancta lucia habet contra fluxum sanguinis opem ferre...'.</note>
                        <note>The following texts are not printed by Graesse:</note>
                        <msItem>
                           <locus>(fols. 183va-184ra)</locus>
                           <rubric>De sancta barbara</rubric>
                           <incipit>Temporibus maximiniani imperatoris erat vir quidam nomine dyoscorus</incipit>
                           <explicit>in habitaculum modicum in quo et sanaciones plurime celebrantur in laudem et gloriam omnipotentis dei cui et honor <gap reason="editorial"/></explicit>
                           <bibl type="repertory"><ref target="https://clavis.brepols.net/clacla/OA/link.aspx?clavis=BHL&amp;number=913"><title>BHL</title> 913</ref></bibl>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem>
                           <locus>(fol. 184ra-b)</locus>
                           <rubric>Miraculum</rubric>
                           <incipit>Legitur quod quidam christiani ciuitatem in qua beata barbara nata fuit passa et sepulta manu armata cepissent </incipit>
                           <explicit>conscripsit ad honorem beate barbare virginis gloriose</explicit>
                           <note>Begins as <ref target="https://clavis.brepols.net/clacla/OA/link.aspx?clavis=BHL&amp;number=929"><title>BHL</title> 929</ref> (abbrev.), followed by a miracle of a beheaded merchant (resembling <ref target="https://clavis.brepols.net/clacla/OA/link.aspx?clavis=BHL&amp;number=940"><title>BHL</title> 940</ref> only very broadly).</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem>
                           <locus>(fols. 185ra-vb)</locus>
                           <rubric>De concepcione marie</rubric>
                           <msItem>
                              <incipit>Eo tempore quo Wilhelmus dux nortmanorum potentissimus prostrato anglorum rege</incipit>
                              <explicit>post hanc vitam requies eternam. Amen.</explicit>
                              <author key="person_280344084"><supplied>Ps.-Anselm</supplied></author>
                              <title key="work_6459"><supplied>Miraculum de conceptione beatae Mariae</supplied></title>
                              <!-- http://www.mirabileweb.it/title/miraculum-de-conceptione-sanctae-mariae-anselmus-c-title/125037 -->
                              <note>PL 159.323</note>
                           </msItem>
                           <msItem>
                              <incipit>Liber generacionis Iesu <gap reason="editorial"/> Maria ut plerique estimant interpretatur illuminatrix uel stella maris</incipit>
                              <explicit>ab omni tristicia seculi <unclear>sunt</unclear> liberati in eterna beatitudine regnare cum christo mereamur</explicit>
                              <note>PL 114.859, a passage from <persName key="person_47555113">Walafrid Strabo</persName>, <title>Homilia in initium evangelii sancti Matthaei</title></note>
                           </msItem>
                           <note> Followed by a note that whoever fasts on the vigil and feast of the conception is delivered from all evil, etc.</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem>
                           <note>(fol. 214vb)</note>
                           <note>Gertrude</note>
                           <incipit>Gerdrudis virgo, venerabilis nobilibus ac religiosis orta parentibus</incipit>
                           <explicit> filium suum ministrare constituit</explicit>
                           <note>Apparently as in <bibl subtype="external" type="ms">Fribourg L 743</bibl> fols. 123v-124, <ref target="https://clavis.brepols.net/clacla/OA/link.aspx?clavis=BHL&amp;number=inedits"><title>BHL</title> inedits</ref>.</note>
                        </msItem>
                        <msItem>
                           <locus>(fol. 228va)</locus>
                           <note>Passion of St George</note>
                           <incipit>Tempore illo rex Dacianus qui erat christianorum persecutor posuit tribunal suum</incipit>
                           <explicit> nona die kalendae may in christo ...</explicit>
                           <note>Perhaps as <bibl subtype="external" type="ms">Frankfurt am Main SUB Praed. 43</bibl>, fols. 64v-65, <ref target="https://clavis.brepols.net/clacla/OA/link.aspx?clavis=BHL&amp;number=inedits"><title>BHL</title> inedits</ref>.</note>
                        </msItem>
